social_posts.post_text: October things with our little pumpkin head 🎃🧡

Happy birthday to our big two year old! Logan, you are such a gift, you bring us so much joy and we couldn’t be more thankful God gave you to us. Today was such a special day celebrating with friends and family, I just want to press rewind and relive it again and again. 💙

It felt so good to race again this weekend! I’ve missed it so much and had the worst itch to get back at it again this last spring but I knew I’m in a season of life where training time is much more limited than it used to be. The 10k training schedule worked out really well for where I am currently and I had a lot of fun with it over the summer. I’m so proud of my effort and performance yesterday. I was able to execute the strategy I had planned and it paid off with hitting my goal of sub-50. This was my first race since having Logan and seeing him at the finish line was such a special experience. I hope I can inspire him to do tough things and stick to his passions in life 🧡 p.s. thank you @steven_robillard & Roy for getting up at the crack of dawn on a Sunday to cheer me on, it means so much to me!
